    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-14T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-14T14:00:00-05:00" n="919"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d919">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/7–1454: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-14T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 14, 1954—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 608. Repeated information Paris 59.
                    Limit distribution. Eyes only <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName>.
                        <persName corresp="#p_OR1">Offroy</persName> informs us that in course of
                    conversation between members of French Delegation and <persName
                        corresp="#p_WPN1">Wang Ping-nan</persName>, Secretary General of Chinese
                    Communist Delegation, latter referred to discussions between <persName
                        corresp="#p_PVD1">Dong</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MFP1"
                        >Mendes-France</persName> re demarcation line (<gloss target="#t_Secto1"
                        >Secto</gloss> 604<note n="1" xml:id="d919fn1">Dated July 14, <ref
                            target="#pg_1368">p. 1368</ref>.</note>). <persName corresp="#p_WPN1"
                        >Wang Ping-nan</persName> stated that French should make some further
                    concession <pb facs="1400" n="1374" xml:id="pg_1374"/> and implied that Viet
                    Minh would be prepared to meet this with even greater concession. French
                    representatives reiterated firm position re Dong Hoi line.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BPW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonsal</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
